    "The discrete wavelet transform (DWT) is a way of decomposing a signal into its wavelet structure while preserving spatial and temporal information 31, 32.",
    "The feature extraction stage in the PolynetDWTCADx system replaces the max pooling layer of CNNs.",
    "The system will undergo a transformation to obtain more detailed information about spatial and temporal attributes in the colonoscopy images, a crucial step in the diagnostic process.",
    "The selection of a very simple yet highly effective Haar wavelet facilitates the extraction and transformation of features.",
    "We subsequently used the outputs of the DWT as inputs for an SVM to enhance multiclass classification, thereby improving differentiation and detection of colorectal cancer."
